<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861203-0102 </DOCNO><HL> Mylex Corp. ChairmanSells 32% of CommonTo Investor Group</HL><DD> 12/03/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MYLXTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> MIAMI  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Mylex Corp. said Anastasios N. Kyriakides, its principal shareholder, chairman and president, sold 3,220,000 shares, or about 32% of the shares outstanding, to a group led by M. Akram Chowdry.    Mr. Chowdry said changes in management and the board are &quot;in progress and should be completed this week,&quot; but declined to elaborate.    The computer products concern said Mr. Kyriakides, who held a total of 4,220,000 shares, still owns one million shares, or about 10% of the shares outstanding. Terms of the sale, on Nov. 26., weren't disclosed.    Mylex said the purchasing group includes employees of the company and individuals in senior management positions in the high-tech and investment industries. The company said Mr. Chowdry is chairman and president of Prime Circuit Technology Inc., a San Jose, Calif.-based maker of electronic products. </TEXT></DOC>